---
description: Performance standards and optimization rules
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
alwaysApply: true
---

# Core Web Vitals Targets
- LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
- FID/INP (Interaction to Next Paint): < 200ms
- CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1

# Loading Performance
- Lazy load routes: React.lazy() + Suspense
- Lazy load below-fold images: loading="lazy" or Intersection Observer
- Critical CSS inlined, non-critical loaded async
- Fonts: Preload critical fonts, use font-display: swap

# Bundle Size
- Import only used functions from libraries (tree-shaking)
- NO entire lodash import — use lodash-es or specific functions
- Analyze bundle with @next/bundle-analyzer or vite-bundle-visualizer

# Runtime Performance
- Memoize expensive computations: useMemo for calculations
- Memoize callbacks passed to children: useCallback
- Virtualize long lists: react-window or @tanstack/react-virtual
- Debounce search inputs: 300ms delay
- Throttle scroll/resize handlers: 16ms (60fps)

# Image Optimization
- Use WebP/AVIF formats with JPEG fallbacks
- Proper sizing: srcset for responsive images
- Placeholder: blur-up or dominant color while loading

# React Specific
- NO anonymous functions in JSX props (creates new reference every render)
- Split context providers — don't put everything in one context
- Use production builds for profiling: React Profiler to find issues
